      • Interval

        public Interval(long startMillis,
                long endMillis)
         throws org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException
        Method creates an object of a time-interval, based on a start and end time.
        Parameters:
        startMillis - is the start time in milliseconds. Must be less or equal than the end time.
        endMillis - is the end time in milliseconds. Must be greater or equal than the start time.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException - is thrown in case the start time is bigger than the end time.

      • getOverlap

        public Interval getOverlap(Interval interval)
                    throws org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException
        Method returns the overlap time of this interval and the input interval, if there is an overlap. Otherwise returns null.
        Parameters:
        interval - is the another interval.
        Returns:
        a interval object, which is the overlap of the intervals. Returns null if there is no overlap.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException - is thrown in case the input interval is null or the start/end times are invalid.

      • overlaps

        public boolean overlaps(Interval interval)
                 throws org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException
        Method compares this interval with the input interval, if there is an overlap.
        Parameters:
        interval - is the another time interval.
        Returns:
        true if the intervals overlap. Otherwise false.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException - is thrown in case the input interval is null.
